                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.338,
                                "byte_start": 73669,
                                "byte_stop": 115047,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in 74-944, Time Incorporated against Firestone, will be announced by Mr. Justice Rehnquist."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.338,
                        "stop": 140.639,
                        "byte_start": 115047,
                        "byte_stop": 636242,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15141,
                            "name": "William H. Rehnquist",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/william_h_rehnquist",
                            "last_name": "Rehnquist",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2787,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 63612000,
                                    "date_end": 528094800,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2787"
                                },
                                {
                                    "id": 2788,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 528094800,
                                    "date_end": 1125723600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Chief Justice of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2788"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32786,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 46923,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/william_rehnquist.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12293,
                            "identifier": "william_h_rehnquist"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.338,
                                "stop": 14.627,
                                "byte_start": 115047,
                                "byte_stop": 132183,
                                "text": "Petitioner is a publisher of the Time Magazine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.627,
                                "stop": 25.566,
                                "byte_start": 132183,
                                "byte_stop": 175965,
                                "text": "That magazine published an article which purported to describe respondent\u2019s divorce from her husband, a member of one of America\u2019s wealthy or industrial family."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.566,
                                "stop": 32.393,
                                "byte_start": 175965,
                                "byte_stop": 203341,
                                "text": "Respondent, claiming the article was both false and defamatory, brought a liable action in a Florida Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.393,
                                "stop": 40.244,
                                "byte_start": 203341,
                                "byte_stop": 234688,
                                "text": "The jury awarded her damages in the amount of a $100,000 and this judgment was ultimately affirmed by the Supreme Court of Florida."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.244,
                                "stop": 48.501,
                                "byte_start": 234688,
                                "byte_stop": 267707,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to consider petitioner\u2019s contentions that this decision infringed its rights under the First and Fourteenth Amendments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 48.501,
                                "stop": 61.158,
                                "byte_start": 267707,
                                "byte_stop": 318384,
                                "text": "For the reasons expressed in an opinion which has been filed with a clerk this morning, we reject petitioner\u2019s arguments that it was entitled for the protection of the standard announced by the court in New York Times versus Sullivan."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 61.158,
                                "stop": 76.613,
                                "byte_start": 318384,
                                "byte_stop": 380138,
                                "text": "We conclude respondent was not a public figure within the meaning of our decisions and we disagree with petitioner\u2019s claim that the New York Times privilege should automatically extend to articles which are reports of judicial proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 76.613,
                                "stop": 87.881,
                                "byte_start": 380138,
                                "byte_stop": 425277,
                                "text": "We hold instead that the proper standard of constitutional protection to be applied in this case is the one we announced two terms ago in Gertz versus Robert Welch."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 87.881,
                                "stop": 93.269,
                                "byte_start": 425277,
                                "byte_stop": 446802,
                                "text": "Our review of the record is satisfied as the two of the elements required by Gertz."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.269,
                                "stop": 100.045,
                                "byte_start": 446802,
                                "byte_stop": 473865,
                                "text": "First that the published report be false and that the damages be supported by competent evidence have been met."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 100.045,
                                "stop": 113.994,
                                "byte_start": 473865,
                                "byte_stop": 529662,
                                "text": "As to Gertz\u2019s third requirement however, it appears that there has never been a finding by another state courts which have considered this case to the effect that petitioner was at fault in preparing and publishing its report of the respondent\u2019s divorce."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.994,
                                "stop": 122.312,
                                "byte_start": 529662,
                                "byte_stop": 562995,
                                "text": "We therefore remand the case to the Supreme Court of Florida in order that this essential element maybe considered and resolved in the state court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.312,
                                "stop": 127.636,
                                "byte_start": 562995,
                                "byte_stop": 584311,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Powell has filed a concurring opinion in which Mr. Justice Stewart has joined."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.636,
                                "stop": 135.611,
                                "byte_start": 584311,
                                "byte_stop": 616180,
                                "text": "Separate dissenting opinions have been filed by Mr. Justice Brennan, Mr. Justice White and Mr. Justice Marshall."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.611,
                                "stop": 140.639,
                                "byte_start": 616180,
                                "byte_stop": 636242,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Stevens took no part in the consideration or decision of this case."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
